io.github.goodees.ese.core.store

Interface EventLog

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    InMemoryEventStore, JdbcEventLog

    public interface EventLog
    Reads persisted logs. This interface is usually implemented along with EventStore, and it defines entity-specific (de)serialization routines.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  EventLog.StoredEvents<E extends Event>
      Accessor that enables single iteration over found events.

    • Method Detail

      • readEvents

        EventLog.StoredEvents<? extends Event> readEvents(String entityId,
                                                  long afterVersion)
        Read all events for an entity that happened after specified version.
        Parameters:
        entityId - the id of an entity
        afterVersion - events that happened after this version. 0 stands for uninitialized, will therefore return entire history
        Returns:
        accessor for the events in order they appeared in history

      • confirmsEntityReflectsCurrentState

        boolean confirmsEntityReflectsCurrentState(EventSourcedEntity entity)
        Compare the version of an entity with the state known in the log. This is used by EventSourcingRuntimeBase to prevent passing requests to an entity that is stale.
        Parameters:
        entity - entity instance
        Returns:
        true if no newer events are known for the entity
        See Also:
        EventSourcedEntity.getIdentity(), EventSourcedEntity.getStateVersion()
